
Welcome to Windows API for Red Team - Introduction.


What you'll learn:
The structure and internals of Win32 and NT APIs
How to develop red team tools using C++ and Assembly
Advanced evasion techniques (unhooking, syscall stubs, NTDLL remapping)
How to develop and interact with basic Windows kernel drivers
Real-world offensive use cases with stealth-focused techniques
Everything will be delivered with practical examples, hands-on code, and references to real-world tools and techniques used by advanced threat actors and security researchers.

Recommended Prerequisites
Basic knowledge of C or C++
Windows 10/11 environment with Visual Studio
Understanding of OS concepts: processes, memory, privileges
Optional: familiarity with x86/x64 Assembly and Windows Internals
